App Service Environments (ASEs) are a premium offering from App Service that provide dedicated resources for hosting your web applications. ASEs are designed for high-traffic, mission-critical applications that require a high level of performance and availability. ASEs provide a dedicated pool of resources, including CPU, memory, and network bandwidth, that are not shared with other customers.
In summary, App Service Plans define the resources and capabilities that are available to your web applications, while App Service Environments provide dedicated resources for hosting high-traffic, mission-critical applications. Just-in-time compilation: This technique compiles the program on-the-fly, which can improve the efficiency of the program by optimizing the code for the specific hardware and software environment.
